On Holocaust Remembrance Day, President Obama issued a statement to honor the memory of the six million Jews and millions of others who were murdered by the Nazis during the Holocaust. He emphasized the importance of never forgetting the atrocities that took place and reaffirmed the responsibility of citizens and the nation to live by the admonition of "Never forget. Never again." The President also highlighted the need to preserve the memories of Holocaust survivors and their experiences, so that future generations do not forget. He commended the courageous individuals who risked their lives to save Jews and other victims from Nazi persecution and emphasized the importance of confronting persecution wherever it arises. The President expressed solidarity with the Jewish community both at home and abroad and called upon people of goodwill to stand against all forms of bigotry. He concluded by emphasizing the importance of recognizing our interconnectedness and working towards a more accepting, secure, and free world.